Build fixes

vp9hdec: Cast ABS parameter to int to avoid C++11's `double abs(Integral)`

C++11 added an overload of abs with return type double for any
Integral parameter type in math.h.  This overload matches more
closely than the `int abs(int)` overload from stdlib.h if the
parameter type happens to be an integral type that isn't int (like
short for example, and ignoring long and long long here).

So to pick the `int abs(int)` overload we need to explicitly cast
ABS's parameter to int.

config/make: fix libcmrt library checking and linkage

Autoconf needs to look for libcmrt, not cmrt.

In the makefile, pass $(driver_libs) to hybrid_drv_video_LIBADD,
not $(driver_files).  Also, don't hardcode -llibcmrt into flags...
it's the wrong thing to do.  Autoconf does this correctly and
places the result in CMRT_LIBS.

Merge pull request #10 from wlin70/fix-crash-resolution-change

vp9hdec: fix crash accessing reference frame's CmSurface2D

vp9hdec: fix crash accessing reference frame's CmSurface2D

Top decoder may call vaDestroy/CreateContext to recreate media ctx and MdfDevice
if target frame size becomes larger.
CmSurface2D of each reference frame will be reclaimed sequentially and segment fault
accessing them.

Fix by using TSC and CmDevice pointer to detect context change and reallocate these CmSurface2D.

Signed-off-by: Wei Lin <wei.w.lin@intel.com>

Merge pull request #9 from wlin70/fix_BAC_SegFault-viz5944

vp9_hdec: fix segment fault on CPBAC engine filling compressed bit st

vp9_hdec: fix segment fault on CPBAC engine filling compressed bit stream.

     (1) Below commit fixed the seg fault, but regression happened.
               "
                commit 680819ffb987bc2ceacfb49b2b278e70df97d84e
                Author: Zhao Yakui <yakui.zhao@intel.com>

                This is to follow what is done in VP9 reference code and avoid the cross
                boundary issue when reading data from compressed bits. Otherwise it
                will trigger the segment fault issue when playing back some VP9 clips.
                "
     (2) Two main changes in this fix:
         1. BAC filling function adds a buf length checking and a byte-read for the last even byte to avoid segfault.
         2. BAC init function applys above filling function if the bit stream buf length is less than 4-byte.
     (3) Referencing libvpx::vp9_reader.c::vp9_reader_fill().

Signed-off-by: Wei Lin <wei.w.lin@intel.com>
